pull_request.title: Stable release
pull_request.body:
This pull request introduces significant improvements to project documentation, developer tooling, and workflow automation for the Svelte portfolio application. The most notable changes include a comprehensive new `README.md`, a detailed backend project reference, a CSS analysis report, and new configuration files for Prettier and VSCode to ensure code consistency and formatting. Additionally, a GitHub Actions workflow is added to automate the generation and updating of design tokens.

**Documentation Enhancements:**

- Added a detailed `README.md` that covers features, installation, architecture, scripts, design system, configuration, testing, deployment, development guidelines, troubleshooting, and contributing instructions for the Svelte portfolio application.
- Introduced `backend/docs/BACK_END_PROJECT_REFERENCE.md`, outlining the current backend status, future plans, recommended technologies, implementation phases, and integration strategies.
- Added `CSS_Analysis_Summary.md` with a comprehensive analysis of Svelte component CSS usage, custom properties (design tokens), and component organization.

**Developer Tooling and Code Formatting:**

- Added `.prettierrc` configuration to enforce consistent code formatting, including Svelte-specific plugin settings.
- Added `.vscode/settings.json` to set Prettier as the default formatter and enable format-on-save for Svelte files.

**Workflow Automation:**

- Added `.github/workflows/generate-tokens.yml` GitHub Actions workflow to automate the generation of design tokens from Figma and create pull requests for token updates.

pull_request.title: Fix QueryJob total_rows attribute error
pull_request.body:
# Fix QueryJob total_rows attribute error ## Summary This PR fixes a critical `AttributeError` that occurs when the BigQuery API returns a `QueryJob` object without the `total_rows` attribute. The error `'QueryJob' object has no attribute 'total_rows'` was causing the application to crash when users asked questions like "how many republicans are there". **Root Cause:** The BigQuery `QueryJob` object doesn't always populate the `total_rows` attribute, particularly for certain query types (like COUNT queries) or under specific conditions. The code was attempting to access this attribute directly, causing an AttributeError. **Fix:** Changed from direct attribute access `query_job.total_rows` to safe access using `getattr(query_job, 'total_rows', None)`, which returns None if the attribute doesn't exist rather than raising an exception. ## Review & Testing Checklist for Human - [ ] **Critical**: Test end-to-end with actual BigQuery queries that return results (not just permission errors) to verify the fix works and doesn't break normal functionality - [ ] **High**: Verify truncation detection still works correctly when `total_rows` is available vs when it's None - [ ] **Medium**: Test various query types (SELECT, COUNT, aggregations, complex queries) to ensure consistent behavior across different BigQuery response patterns **Recommended Test Plan:** 1. Run the agent CLI with COUNT queries: "how many republicans are there" 2. Run regular SELECT queries to ensure truncation detection still works 3. Try various query patterns to verify no regression in functionality --- ### Diagram ```mermaid %%{ init : { "theme" : "default" }}%% graph TD CLI["app_cli.py"]:::context --> Agent["agent.py"]:::context Agent --> BQTool["bigquery_tool.py"]:::minor-edit BQTool --> BQClient["BigQuery Client"]:::context BQTool --> TotalRowsFix["Safe total_rows access
using getattr()"]:::minor-edit TotalRowsFix --> TruncationLogic["Truncation Detection
Logic"]:::context subgraph Legend L1[Major Edit]:::major-edit L2[Minor Edit]:::minor-edit L3[Context/No Edit]:::context end classDef major-edit fill:#90EE90 classDef minor-edit fill:#87CEEB classDef context fill:#FFFFFF ``` ### Notes - **Testing Limitation**: Due to BigQuery permission constraints in the development environment, I could only verify that error handling works correctly. Full end-to-end testing with successful queries is needed. - **Previous PR Issue**: This fix was supposedly included in PR #57 which shows as "Merged", but the fix didn't make it to main properly, suggesting there may have been a merge issue. - **Change Impact**: Minimal code change (2 lines) but affects a critical path in query result processing. **Session Info**: Requested by Greg (gregtusar@gmail.com) **Link to Devin run**: https://app.devin.ai/sessions/70ba3ae6fc8d46b48eb248b1e5354fd1
